AN ACT relating to public utilities; requiring the Public Utilities Commission of
Nevada to open one or more investigatory dockets to examine certain
matters relating to a potential cost-sharing adjustment mechanism;
requiring a utility to refund certain overcharges; revising provisions
governing certain applications filed by a public utility; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Section 1.3 of this bill requires the Public Utilities Commission of Nevada to open one or
2 more investigatory dockets to examine certain matters relating to a potential cost-sharing
3 adjustment mechanism for the recovery of costs for purchased fuel and purchased power and
4 the sharing of such costs between an electric utility and its customers. Section 1.3 requires the
5 Commission to submit periodic reports to the Joint Interim Standing Committee on Growth
6 and Infrastructure concerning the progress of each investigatory docket and, on or before July
7 1, 2026, submit a final report to the Legislative Commission on the outcomes of the
8 investigatory dockets. Under section 1.3, the Commission is authorized to adopt regulations to
9 establish a cost-sharing adjustment mechanism, if the Commission finds it is in the public
10 interest as a result of the investigatory docket.
11 If the Commission determines that a utility has charged a customer more than any
12 applicable rate or tariff allows, section 1.7 of this bill requires a utility to refund to the
13 customer, with interest, the full amount of any overcharge.
14 Existing law requires the Commission to issue a written order approving or disapproving
15 an application filed by a public utility to make any change in a schedule not later than 210
16 days after the date on which the application is filed. (NRS 704.110) Section 2 of this bill
17 [authorizes] requires the Commission, [under certain circumstances, to extend by not more
18 than 90 days the time to act on such] for an application filed by certain electric utilities [.] , to
19 issue such a written order not later than 300 days after the date on which the application
20 is filed.

